wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.jpg?w=1674&amp;ssl=1 1674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-86500\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Ollie Tabooger / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hello again Recruiter,</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thank you for getting back to me after two and a half months! I really appreciate you taking the time out of your hectic day and clearly busy quarter to come back around and talk to me, a lowly interviewee. I would love to go in for a third round of interviews, especially since I’ve only interviewed with a single member from your firm!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please let me know the appropriate procedure following this email.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thank you,</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don</span></p>\n<div id=\"attachment_86501\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-86501\" data-attachment-id=\"86501\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2019-02-27/letters-to-my-lover-recruiter/3-6/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?fit=1674%2C1114&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1674,1114\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"3\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?fit=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?fit=888%2C591&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"wp-image-86501 size-large\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-1024x681.jpg?resize=888%2C591\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"591\" srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?resize=1024%2C681&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?resize=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?resize=768%2C511&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg?w=1674&amp;ssl=1 1674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-86501\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Ollie Tabooger / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dear Recruiter,</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I’ve now interviewed a total of four times with your firm. Each conversation I have had has been increasingly encouraging — both the managers and partners have expressed interest in me joining your team. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Again, I am willing to do anything you ask for this job. Please just pay me. I’m desperate. Help me. Please. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thanks,</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mr. Chawanmi</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">P.S. Also, your firm is actually great and I REALLY want to work for you. Please!</span></p>\n<div id=\"attachment_86502\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-86502\" data-attachment-id=\"86502\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2019-02-27/letters-to-my-lover-recruiter/4-6/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?fit=1674%2C1114&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1674,1114\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"4\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?fit=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?fit=888%2C591&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"wp-image-86502 size-large\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-1024x681.jpg?resize=888%2C591\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"591\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?resize=1024%2C681&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?resize=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?resize=768%2C511&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg?w=1674&amp;ssl=1 1674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-86502\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Ollie Tabooger / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hi Recruiter,</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You piece of shit.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You made me excited after your recruiting event. Had me wait for three months to finish an interview process that should have concluded in three weeks. Made me hopeful for future employment with your firm. But you just straight-up led me on.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What kind of behavior is this?! Haven’t you ever heard of treating others how you want to be treated? I am only human after all.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I thought we had a connection, but it has now been deeply severed. I don’t know why I took part in this manipulative relationship. You just dragged me along for the ride because you thought I was easy, didn’t you? Well, I’m here to tell you that’s not okay and I am profoundly offended by your fake niceties.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Consider this our official break-up. I know we were never dating, but I felt a connection to you unmatched to anything I’ve experienced in the past. Please know I still respect you, even though I feel you don’t respect me. My loyalty lies with you, and if you ever have an opening for me I will take it because I am emotionally unwell. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anyways, I hope you have a great fucking life without me — but also, I love you. I’ll never stop loving you. Please don’t hate me.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Warmest Regards,</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don Chawanmi</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don Chawanmi hopes to be loved again in the same way this recruiter faked their love to him.</span></i></p><div class=\"h5ab-print-button-container\"><div class=\"h5ab-print-button h5ab-print-button-left\" style=\"cursor: pointer; color: #555\"><i class=\"fa fa-print fa-lg\"></i>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span>Print</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon sd-sharing\"><h3 class=\"sd-title\">Share this:</h3><div class=\"sd-content\"><ul><li class=\"share-facebook\"><a rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-shared=\"sharing-facebook-86498\" class=\"share-facebook sd-button share-icon no-text\" href=\"https://dailynexus.com/2019-02-27/letters-to-my-lover-recruiter/?share=facebook\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Facebook\"><span></span><span class=\"sharing-screen-reader-text\">Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window)</span></a></li><li class=\"share-twitter\"><a rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-shared=\"sharing-twitter-86498\" class=\"share-twitter sd-button share-icon no-text\" href=\"https://dailynexus.com/2019-02-27/letters-to-my-lover-recruiter/?share=twitter\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Twitter\"><span></span><span class=\"sharing-screen-read